  "prompt": "My sister was forcefully asked to resign just because she was on bench for a month after her training. How can I fight this injustice?",
  "response": "Here are some steps you can take to address this situation:\n\n1. Legal steps:\n- Consult an employment lawyer\n- Check if the resignation was lawful\n- Determine if there's a case for wrongful termination\n- Review her employment contract\n\n2. Documentation evidence:\n- Collect all written communication\n- Gather performance records\n- Get details about the bench period\n- Compile reasons given for forced resignation\n\n3. Organizational approaches:\n- File a formal complaint with HR\n- Escalate to higher management\n- Request detailed explanation in writing\n- Check company's policies regarding bench periods\n\n4. External support:\n- Contact labor department\n- Approach labor commission\n- Seek advice from professional employment forums\n- Consider filing a complaint with relevant labor authorities\n\n5. Additional recommendations:\n- Remain professional\n- Document all communications\n- Preserve email/message trails\n- Consider seeking mediation\n- Explore potential job market opportunities\n\n6. Evidence gathering:\n- Collect witness statements\n- Get performance reviews\n- Note timeline of events\n- Identify potential discrimination factors\n\nEach situation is unique, so professional legal consultation would provide the most accurate guidance specific to your sister's case.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
